A gentle caress along my cheek
Makes my knees grow weak

Without a soft cushion to land

You caress my lower back, sending electricity throughout my body

I gaze at you -- all the while you're not knowing what your touch does to me

I'm in awe of your sensuality

I want badly to kiss your lips, but bravery has escaped my grasp

It was only a dream

I've tasted what I thought was the finer things in life
I've awakened to smell those prickly roses
I've drank the bitter black coffee you've made

But none of it was for me

Obligated
Complicated
Irritated
Aggravated

Synonyms I relate to

What a life
of uselessness

He loves the taste of her on his tongue

The saltiness of her skin

The sweet and sensual scent of vanilla and honey perfume

She satisfied his craving

Awakened his senses

He wanted her

Craved her

Needed her body against his own

In succulent & deep embrace

We did a bad thing -- But we never spoke a word of it. 

The town found out with us not knowing through whom.

That grapevine can be sneaky.

Secrets are not easily kept in a borough of nosey neighbors.

Perhaps we appear guilty.

We will wear their blood on our hands.
